His eyes where beginning to glaze over. He didn't want to leave, he didn't want to ship. He wanted to remain in the unknown paradise for as long as possible. Trouble was the unknown paridise would not remain viable where it to remain unknown and so he sat. Sat well beyond what his expense account would cover. Hell, well beyond what common decency would cover. It was hard to find a consistant way to bill for an emotional consultancy and his crotch burned with the disatifaction of perpetual rebuttal. 

Gymwise Rooster was out on a limb. Quite literally. It was the only way across the ford and he was beginning to realise why his species had traditionally stuck to their own side of the river. It wasnt a decision he had taken lightly.